<br>
This question has already been answered by at least 2 other games, and it works very well. As far as the economy goes, eq has the second worst economy of orpg's. What items are nodrop?<br>
<br>
1. Quest items.<br>
2. High level/worth items.<br>
<br>
Also, pvp wouldn't want to lose their most prized possessions.<br>
<br>
3 solutions that are doable in eq atmosphere:<br>
-------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
Solution 1. Quest items.<br>
<br>
The quest system is a mess, however, a couple very simple solutions could solve some problems. Make quest items only drop for people that are involved in the quest. Don't make it drop on the ground, but in their inventory. If you're not on the quest, you don't get the item, plain and simple. Quest items should also be soulbound (non-tradable). (I realize this is still a type of nodrop, but it keeps the farmers from sitting on quests to make money) The uber quest mobs requiring several groups to kill should have a ghost, or an npc that appears after death to hand out the quest item to those requiring it. This npc would only be up for a minute or two, for those dying and needing a res to collect. Any major quest items can only be gotten once, and only if you are at that stage in the quest. As far as more than one person receiving the quest item per mob death, I believe that should be up for discussion as some quests would be ok, but others not.<br>
<br>
Solution 2. High Level/Worth items.<br>
<br>
Make items have level limits. This was also brought up by many in this forum. Pretty simple fix.<br>
<br>
Solution 3. PvP<br>
<br>
Introduce a spell, or npc's that can soulbind items to you. You would be able to bind up to 5? items to you that can never be taken from you. Should make it reversible by owner.<br>
<br>
I think that should cover it. Let me know of any problems I hadn't thought of. <p><br><img
